The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 New Delhi, Dec 21 (PTI): The finance ministry has allowed customers to use the unique identification authoritys Aadhaar number to open bank accounts.           
	The authority said the notification would give the poor easier access to finance by making it possible to establish their identity. Sources said the move would boost the popularity of the Aadhaar project.                   
	New Delhi (PTI): Government servants who have been wrongly denied promotion in service can claim its benefit even after retirement, the Central Administrative Tribunal has ruled. Two retired employees of the commerce department had petitioned the tribunal seeking retrospective promotions.                   
	Stockholm (AP): A shopkeeper of Indian origin who gave police video footage of the Stockholm suicide bombing has been told to dismantle his security cameras because he lacks the proper permit. Naresh Lakhwani said police had thanked him for the tape.                   
	 Jammu (PTI): Three Pakistani military helicopter violated Indian airspace over Jammu, officials said on Tuesday. The aircraft flew very low over the Abdulliyan post before turning back towards Sialkot. Further details are yet to be disclosed.                   
	Udhagamandalam (PTI): A herd of elephants trampled a 60-year-old man to death and injured his wife after straying into their estate in Tamil Nadu, police said on Tuesday.                                                                                                                                              
